![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d2e3fe59-c67f-410f-8b7c-7fa98bcd80a0/17156.jpg)

Hangman Adam Page and Kyle Fletcher open Dynamite with a Contract signing for the AEW World Championship at All In.

Don Callis tries to rile Hangman up but Page speaks directly to Kyle Fletcher. Hangman says he can easily beat up the Don Callis Family but if Fletcher is worth becoming World Champion, he's going to have to do this alone.

If the DCF helps Kyle Fletcher, he will be stripped of the TNT Championship. Callis is furious. But Fletcher is confident. He says he would've dragged his body through glass to become Men's World Champion.

He is better than Hangman in 2019, 2021 and he's damn sure better than Hangman right now. AEW doesn't need Hangman or Kenny Omega. It needs the Protostar.

Hangman believes Kyle Fletcher when he says he will bring everything he has but it will not be enough.

What Kyle Fletcher does with the feeling of his loss in the days after All Out will be what defines him. Hangman hopes Kyle Fletcher won't disappoint him.

